(88, 1, '2018-09-24 15:15:05', '2018-09-24 12:15:05', '<span class=\"a-size-base review-text\" data-hook=\"review-body\">This is a super value, a full-size 88-key digital piano that works very well. Sound quality is excellent; the piano &amp; other patches are solid. Key action is in between a keyboard &amp; hammer-action; good spring action. It\'s full-size fun. At 15 pounds, it\'s solid and doesn\'t slip around, it\'s built strong and sturdy.\r\n\r\nI\'ve been a lifelong keyboard player, since my Roland D-50 and Alesis HR16/MMT8 in the 80s (all of which still work fine).\r\n\r\nI was looking for a starter digital piano, and this one is a new release. I normally never buy new-release Anything with no reviews. but I thought I\'d take a chance on this, and I\'m glad I did. Just got it today and thought I\'d write this to help anyone on the fence (and as a thanks to Alesis, I\'ve enjoyed the HR16/MMT8 drum mach/sequencer for decades).\r\n\r\nThe 2 main criteria I wanted are:\r\n\r\na) piano sound: how realistic, the timbre and depth? This one is as good or better than my $1k pro keyboards. I\'ll likely make a review video soon so you can all hear. Much better than expected piano sound; pro-quality at a consumer price, super value.\r\n\r\nb) key action: how solid, responsive, playable? I\'m impressed, very pro build quality, solid and fun to play. I\'ve just played it 2 hours today and am thrilled. Solid, responsive and sounds great. And I really like they are full-size keys, a must.\r\n\r\nI like the ease-of-use in layering 2 patches (like piano/synth), for different sounds; for variety, though mostly all I care about is the piano sound, which is superb. . Walter, your product review video sold me; thanks Alesis team for an affordable high-quality dp. Also the velocity sensitivity is excellent, a must-have for a digital piano.\r\n\r\nHighly recommended, very good playability, tone, features &amp; value. Bravo Alesis, thanks. Worth a lot more than they\'re asking, it\'s a very satisfying instrument at a great price.\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://www.amazon.com/Alesis-Recital-Full-Size-Semi-Weighted-Built/dp/B01DZXE9NC/ref=sr_1_4_acs_osp_osp20-845e6b78-76_2?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1537814111&amp;sr=8-4-acs&amp;keywords=pianos&amp;tag=bestcont06-20&amp;ascsubtag=845e6b78-763a-4f3c-846e-72b9df235ad6&amp;linkCode=oas&amp;cv_ct_id=amzn1.osp.845e6b78-763a-4f3c-846e-72b9df235ad6&amp;cv_ct_pg=search&amp;cv_ct_wn=osp-search&amp;pf_rd_m=ATVPDKIKX0DER&amp;pf_rd_p=bde7b808-4983-454b-9a71-59c1fc01c0c2&amp;pd_rd_wg=QD1Rz&amp;pf_rd_s=desktop-sx-inline&amp;pd_rd_w=jfAnP&amp;pf_rd_i=pianos&amp;pd_rd_r=af19c5ef-4130-4168-9328-c7b5dee5c445&amp;pf_rd_r=Y1P6C2K3H5TX7BNQXDSD&amp;pf_rd_t=301&amp;creativeASIN=B01DZXE9NC&amp;pf_rd_p=bde7b808-4983-454b-9a71-59c1fc01c0c2&amp;pf_rd_m=ATVPDKIKX0DER&amp;pf_rd_s=desktop-sx-inline&amp;pd_rd_r=af19c5ef-4130-4168-9328-c7b5dee5c445&amp;pf_rd_i=pianos&amp;pf_rd_r=Y1P6C2K3H5TX7BNQXDSD&amp;pf_rd_t=301&amp;pd_rd_w=jfAnP&amp;pd_rd_wg=QD1Rz&amp;pd_rd_i=B01DZXE9NC', 'digital piano', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'projection-in-music-industry', '', '', '2018-09-24 21:41:02', '2018-09-24 18:41:02', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=88', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(89, 1, '2018-09-24 15:15:05', '2018-09-24 12:15:05', 'The U.S. live music industry is expected to grow to 11.06 billion by 2019, up from 9.06 in 2014. Music streaming, as of 2015, is at about 3.66B. The rise of festivals is proving to be extremely lucrative not only for big names, but it also gives up-and-coming artists more exposure. ', 'Projection in music industry', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '88-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-24 15:15:05', '2018-09-24 12:15:05', '', 88, 'http://localhost/wordpress/uncategorized/88-revision-v1/.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(90, 1, '2018-09-24 15:17:58', '2018-09-24 12:17:58', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span class=\"a-size-base review-text\" data-hook=\"review-body\">I purchased this keyboard as an absolute beginner to learn to play on as an adult. Knowing I would have limited time to practice I was looking for an affordable option that would not break the bank. After reading other reviews this seemed to be a viable option so I pulled the trigger. So keep in mind that my review comes from the position of an absolute beginner and here are my thoughts...\r\n\r\nThis keyboard is a good option for a beginner to learn on before moving on to a more expensive option if you decide you do enjoy the hobby. The keyboard works exactly as advertised. Nothing more, nothing less. I do feel like anyone with experience playing on a nicer or professional keyboard would not enjoy playing on this one as the keys have a \"toy like\" feel and spring to them. But overall everything works as it should. I\'m not overly blown away, but it gets the job done. I feel certain this will be all the keyboard I need to learn how to properly play music. With that said I will finish off with some pro\'s and con\'s.\r\n\r\nPro\'s:\r\n-Comes with a fairly sturdy stand, nice seat, decent head phones and mic (have not used the mic)\r\n-Lots of different options as far as instruments and backup beats to choose from\r\n-Decent sounding speakers if you choose not to use the headphones\r\n-Keys are easy to play and move freely\r\n-Good beginner setup to learn on\r\n-works as advertised\r\n-items were well packaged\r\n\r\nCon\'s:\r\n-My biggest Con - DOES NOT COME WITH A 10v POWER ADAPTER. There IS a place to plug in a power adapter on the back of the keyboard yet it did NOT come with one in the box. I had to find one from another appliance I had around the house. Yes, you can use this keyboard with batteries but it did not come with those either. I feel like most people would rather plug it in then use batteries. My opinion would have been to leave the mic out and include a power adapter. I think more people would use the adapter then the mic.\r\n-keys seem very toy like. They have a spring like feel to them and are a little noisy\r\n-the music sheet holder sits in the rail very loosely so if you bump it at all it will fall off. Anything heavy falls off.\r\n-when the instrument is set to standard piano, low keys sound fine but the high keys sound a little off, a little digital (no pun intended)\r\n-the on/off button is like something off of an early 1980s toy. It is not a huge deal but it does seem like the one thing that is out of place\r\n\r\nIf they would have included a power adapter and the keys had just slightly better feel, I would have given 5 stars. In the end though I would recommend this for a beginner.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://www.amazon.com/Hamzer-Portable-Electronic-Headphones-Microphone/dp/B0714JFQ7F/ref=sr_1_3?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1537814111&amp;sr=8-3&amp;keywords=pianos', 'Hamzer 61-Key Portable Electronic Keyboard Piano', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'musical-instruments', '', '', '2018-09-24 21:37:33', '2018-09-24 18:37:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=90', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(91, 1, '2018-09-24 15:17:58', '2018-09-24 12:17:58', 'Everyone loves music but have different ways to enjoy it. Either listening to the song, humming the tunes or playing the instruments. Each one has it’s own choice in linking oneself to music. Some of those folks are the ones who actually play an instrument or compose music. It could be as a hobby or as a career choice. This allows them to be a step closer to music. There are hundreds of different kinds of instruments people can learn to play though.\r\n\r\nBeing able to play your favorite instrument has many advantages. Some use it as a pastime, others do this out of passion for music, and for some it’s kinda stress buster or meditation. Millions of people all over the world play all kinds of instruments as a way to express themselves. Others simply do it for entertainment, fun or to earn money. But out of so many, which ones are the most popular instruments that are easy to play? This list shows the top 15 most popular and easiest out of all of them.', 'Musical instruments', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '90-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-24 15:17:58', '2018-09-24 12:17:58', '', 90, 'http://localhost/wordpress/uncategorized/90-revision-v1/.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
