(153, 1, '2018-09-24 21:34:01', '2018-09-24 18:34:01', '<span class=\"a-size-base review-text\" data-hook=\"review-body\">his drum set came as expected and described with all of the needed parts and accessories. I saw some negative feedback from some users out there who seem to expect a lot from a \"Kids\" drum set... I am a music therapist and bought these for my 2 year old daughter... the sound and quality is quite good, especially for the PRICE.. If you are expecting a \"Top of the line\" Tama, Yamaha, or Ludewig set then look elsewhere, this is as stated a kids set... hence the low price, but again if you buy it with the right expectations that it is for a kid, then you will be as happy as I am... the sound, etc are perfectly fine when tuned correctly... I read some people complaining that the instructions were not clean.. Do what I did.... Look on youtube for a video of putting these or a similar set like it together... it worked perfectly for me.. here is one so you do not have to go crazy!\r\n\r\nEnjoy the Set! I do recommend buying it...</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://www.amazon.com/Mendini-Complete-Adjustable-Drumsticks-MJDS-5-BK/dp/B004Z8ORL6/ref=sr_1_10?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1537813921&amp;sr=8-10&amp;keywords=drums', 'drums', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '121-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-24 21:34:01', '2018-09-24 18:34:01', '', 121, 'http://localhost/wordpress/uncategorized/121-revision-v1/.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(154, 1, '2018-09-24 21:35:59', '2018-09-24 18:35:59', 'Everyone loves music but have different ways to enjoy it. Either listening to the song, humming the tunes or playing the instruments. Each one has it’s own choice in linking oneself to music. Some of those folks are the ones who actually play an instrument or compose music. It could be as a hobby or as a career choice. This allows them to be a step closer to music. There are hundreds of different kinds of instruments people can learn to play though.\n\nBeing able to play your favorite instrument has many advantages. Some use it as a pastime, others do this out of passion for music, and for some it’s kinda stress buster or meditation. Millions of people all over the world play all kinds of instruments as a way to express themselves. Others simply do it for entertainment, fun or to earn money. But out of so many, which ones are the most popular instruments that are easy to play? This list shows the top 15 most popular and easiest out of all of them.', 'Hamzer 61-Key Portable Electronic Keyboard Piano with Stand, Stool, H', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '90-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-09-24 21:35:59', '2018-09-24 18:35:59', '', 90, 'http://localhost/wordpress/uncategorized/90-autosave-v1/.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(155, 1, '2018-09-24 21:37:33', '2018-09-24 18:37:33', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span class=\"a-size-base review-text\" data-hook=\"review-body\">I purchased this keyboard as an absolute beginner to learn to play on as an adult. Knowing I would have limited time to practice I was looking for an affordable option that would not break the bank. After reading other reviews this seemed to be a viable option so I pulled the trigger. So keep in mind that my review comes from the position of an absolute beginner and here are my thoughts...\r\n\r\nThis keyboard is a good option for a beginner to learn on before moving on to a more expensive option if you decide you do enjoy the hobby. The keyboard works exactly as advertised. Nothing more, nothing less. I do feel like anyone with experience playing on a nicer or professional keyboard would not enjoy playing on this one as the keys have a \"toy like\" feel and spring to them. But overall everything works as it should. I\'m not overly blown away, but it gets the job done. I feel certain this will be all the keyboard I need to learn how to properly play music. With that said I will finish off with some pro\'s and con\'s.\r\n\r\nPro\'s:\r\n-Comes with a fairly sturdy stand, nice seat, decent head phones and mic (have not used the mic)\r\n-Lots of different options as far as instruments and backup beats to choose from\r\n-Decent sounding speakers if you choose not to use the headphones\r\n-Keys are easy to play and move freely\r\n-Good beginner setup to learn on\r\n-works as advertised\r\n-items were well packaged\r\n\r\nCon\'s:\r\n-My biggest Con - DOES NOT COME WITH A 10v POWER ADAPTER. There IS a place to plug in a power adapter on the back of the keyboard yet it did NOT come with one in the box. I had to find one from another appliance I had around the house. Yes, you can use this keyboard with batteries but it did not come with those either. I feel like most people would rather plug it in then use batteries. My opinion would have been to leave the mic out and include a power adapter. I think more people would use the adapter then the mic.\r\n-keys seem very toy like. They have a spring like feel to them and are a little noisy\r\n-the music sheet holder sits in the rail very loosely so if you bump it at all it will fall off. Anything heavy falls off.\r\n-when the instrument is set to standard piano, low keys sound fine but the high keys sound a little off, a little digital (no pun intended)\r\n-the on/off button is like something off of an early 1980s toy. It is not a huge deal but it does seem like the one thing that is out of place\r\n\r\nIf they would have included a power adapter and the keys had just slightly better feel, I would have given 5 stars. In the end though I would recommend this for a beginner.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://www.amazon.com/Hamzer-Portable-Electronic-Headphones-Microphone/dp/B0714JFQ7F/ref=sr_1_3?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1537814111&amp;sr=8-3&amp;keywords=pianos', 'Hamzer 61-Key Portable Electronic Keyboard Piano', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '90-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-24 21:37:33', '2018-09-24 18:37:33', '', 90, 'http://localhost/wordpress/uncategorized/90-revision-v1/.html', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
